  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Plutarch and Rhetoric, published by Leuven University Press in 2024, is recognized for its commercial potential, reflecting a strong interest in its subject matter. The book is expected to contribute to ongoing discussions about rhetoric in academia, especially given its alignment with sustainability and policy relevance.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The publication of Plutarch and Rhetoric marks a significant contribution to the field of rhetoric studies, poised to generate commercial interest evidenced by its presence on platforms like Amazon and Goodreads. This commercial linkage suggests that the work not only appeals to scholars but also has the potential to reach a broader audience, enhancing its impact within and beyond academic circles.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">In terms of sustainability and policy relevance, the book's inferred strength indicates its contribution to discussions surrounding the United Nations Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs). The engagement with such themes enhances the book\u2019s relevance in the current social and academic discourse, illustrating its alignment with contemporary issues that resonate with a wider audience.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">While specific metrics regarding community engagement or citation are not available at this stage, the absence of mentions on platforms such as Wikipedia or Reddit highlights an opportunity for future discourse surrounding the book. Engaging these platforms could spur public discussions about the themes presented in the book, fostering a dialogue that bridges academic insights with societal implications.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The book's release in 2024 will be crucial for establishing its footprint in both academic and public spheres. Although it currently has no recorded citations or community discussions, its focus on Plutarch and rhetoric is likely to attract attention from both scholars and the public interested in the evolution and significance of rhetorical practices. As the landscape of rhetoric continues to evolve, Plutarch and Rhetoric stands ready to play an active role in these discussions.</p>",
